Adapter-pack plugin — distributes one or more `@adapter`-decorated
recipes that turn website APIs into deterministic, reusable agent tools.

## Install

```bash
# from a local checkout
opencomputer plugin install file:///path/to/{{ plugin_id }}

# from GitHub
opencomputer plugin install github:{{ author }}/{{ plugin_id }}
```

## Layout

```
{{ plugin_id }}/
├── plugin.json           — manifest (kind=tool, entry=plugin)
├── plugin.py             — calls register_adapter_pack on the api
├── adapters/<site>/      — one .py per adapter, plus verify/<name>.json
│   └── example/
│       └── command.py    — sample @adapter
└── README.md             — this file
```

## Authoring

See the `adapter-author` skill bundled with `browser-control` for the
full runbook (recon → write → verify).

Quick start:

```python
from extensions.adapter_runner import adapter, Strategy

@adapter(
    site="example",
    name="command",
    description="...",
    domain="example.com",
    strategy=Strategy.PUBLIC,
    columns=["..."],
)
async def run(args, ctx):
    return await ctx.fetch("https://example.com/api/data")
```

The `adapter-runner` plugin discovers + registers your adapters
automatically on the next agent boot.
